<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="29" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cryptantha dimorpha" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dimorpha">Cryptantha dimorpha</taxonomicName>
≡ 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Eritrichium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eritrichium dimorphum" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dimorphum">Eritrichium dimorphum</taxonomicName>
Phil., Linnaea 29: 16. 1857. Type: Chile. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Región">Region</normalizedToken>
Metropolitana de Santiago: Cordillera de Santiago, Feb. 1857, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">R.A. Philippi s.n</emphasis>
. (lectotype, designated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Johnston, IM" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 118" refId="B16" refString="Johnston, IM, 1927. Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University 78: 1 - 118" title="Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae." volume="78" year="1927">Johnston 1927</bibRefCitation>
, pg. 67: SGO [SGO000004066 digital image!]; isolectotypes: CORD [CORD00003771 digital image!], GH [GH00096384 digital image!], S [S no. 12-25247 digital image!]).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="29" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
<bibRefCitation author="Philippi, RA" journalOrPublisher="INTA, Buenos Aires" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" refId="B34" refString="Philippi, RA, 1857. Plantarum novarum Chilensium: centuria quarta, quinta, sexta. Linnaea 29(1): 1-47, 48-95, 96-110." title="Plantarum novarum Chilensium: centuria quarta, quinta, sexta. Linnaea 29 (1): 1 - 47, 48 - 95, 96 - 110." year="1857">Rudolph A. Philippi (1857)</bibRefCitation>
based the diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Eritrichium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eritrichium dimorphum" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dimorphum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Eritrichium dimorphum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on a collection he made in Santiago, Chile, without explicit further reference to any locality. 
<bibRefCitation author="Johnston, IM" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 118" refId="B16" refString="Johnston, IM, 1927. Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University 78: 1 - 118" title="Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae." volume="78" year="1927">Johnston (1927)</bibRefCitation>
, in his revision of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cryptantha" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Cryptantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in South America, referred to a specimen lodged at SGO as the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“type”">&quot;type&quot;</normalizedToken>
of the name. However, an additional duplicate annotated, in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Philippi’s">Philippi's</normalizedToken>
hand, as &quot; 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Eritrichium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eritrichium dimorphum" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dimorphum">Eritrichium dimorphum</taxonomicName>
&quot;, is found at CORD. Both specimens are in agreement with the diagnosis as referred to by 
<bibRefCitation author="Philippi, RA" journalOrPublisher="INTA, Buenos Aires" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" refId="B34" refString="Philippi, RA, 1857. Plantarum novarum Chilensium: centuria quarta, quinta, sexta. Linnaea 29(1): 1-47, 48-95, 96-110." title="Plantarum novarum Chilensium: centuria quarta, quinta, sexta. Linnaea 29 (1): 1 - 47, 48 - 95, 96 - 110." year="1857">Philippi (1857)</bibRefCitation>
. Therefore, the element cited by Johnston and his statement must be considered as an effective lectotypification of the name.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
